{"text": "(i.e. Eq. 74), which is shown in panel (a) of Fig. 7, confirms the existence of the pair of\n\nzero-energy bound states at phase \u03c6 = \u03c0 on in the topological superconducting (i.e. topo-\n\nlogically nontrivial) phase. The topologically trivial phase shows a gapped spectrum as a\n\nfunction of phase \u03c6 as expected.\n\nWhile the value of phase \u03c6 where the zero-energy crossing occurs is not protected against\n\nchanges in detail of the Hamiltonian of the junction, the crossing itself is protected by\n\nparticle-hole symmetry. Let us start by writing the dispersion of the Andreev bound states\n\n52\n\n(i.e. Eq. 101) near phase \u03c6 \u223c\u03c0 as\n\nE\u00b1 \u2243\u00b1\u03b6(\u03c6 \u2212\u03c0),\n\n(127)\n\nwhere the index \u00b1 refer to the two branches of the spectrum for the topologically nontrivial\n\nphase seen in Fig. 7(a). The level crossing of Andreev states as the phase \u03c6 changes by\n\n2\u03c0 can be understood in terms of the topological invariant in Eq. 45 by considering the\n\ntopological superconductor Josephson junction in a ring. The 2\u03c0 superconducting phase\n\ndifference is generated across the Josephson junction by introducing a superconducting flux\n\nquantum \u03a6 = \u03a60, where \u03a60 is actually half an electron flux quantum 2\u03a60 = hc/e ( by virtue\n\nof the electron charge being half a Cooper pair charge ). Thus, changing the superconducting\n\nphase \u03c6 by 2\u03c0 changes the boundary conditions around the ring from periodic i.e. k = 0\n\nto anti-periodic i.e. k = \u03c0, where k is the wave-vector for Bogoliubov quasiparticles. For\n\ntopological superconductors with a non-trivial value for the topological invariant in Eq. 45,\n\nsuch a change in boundary condition leads to a change in the Pfaffian of the BdG Hamiltonian\n\nwith Josephson junction phase \u03c6 = 0 and \u03c6 = 2\u03c0. This change in the sign of the Pfaffian\n\naccording to Eq.", "embedding": [-0.0015228435, -0.0016936228, 0.